                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="152" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <foliation>Contemporary foliation in brown ink xi-clxii (<locus from="1r" to="152r" scheme="folios"/>).</foliation>
                                    <condition>First quire, consisting of ten leaves, missing. Four holes visible on all quires, through which the ribbons for the seals were originally drawn. Red mould-stains throughout the volume, particularly large on <locus from="36v" to="39r" scheme="folios"/>. On <locus from="20v" to="20v" scheme="folios"/>, the ink has been damaged by damp, but the text is still legible.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="1" writtenLines="15 32">
