                                            <width unit="mm" max="110" min="110"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>Guidelines in lead (not visible on all pages).</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="150r" scheme="folios"/>Hybrida (chancery) with occasional looped ascenders. The scribe is <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102581">Conradus Gregorii</persName>, priest in the diocese of <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100046">Linköping</placeName>, see <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107257">Kolsrud (1935)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="225" to="225" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl> and <bibl>
                                        <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107267">Collijn (1943)</title>
                                        <citedRange from="xxv" to="xxv" unit="page"/>
                                    </bibl>. On <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/> a mention of Conradus as a scribe: <quote xml:lang="la">hoc presens instrumentum publicum instrumentum manu mea fideliter scriptum</quote>.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="150v" to="151r" scheme="folios"/>Hybrida with occasional looped ascenders. The scribe is <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102580">Ingemundus Petri</persName>, priest in the diocese of Linköping. </handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-3">
                                    <locus from="151r" to="151v" scheme="folios"/>Hybrida. The scribe is <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102582">Olaus Johannis</persName>, priest in the diocese of Strängnäs. </handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-4">
                                    <locus from="151v" to="152r" scheme="folios"/>Gothic cursive. The scribe is <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102583">Olaus Andreae</persName>, priest in the diocese of Strängnäs. </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page in pencil by a modern hand: <quote>A 93</quote>, in the outer margin: <quote>1475</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="149v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Marginal annotations in light brown ink by a late medieval hand throughout the volume. According to <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107257">Kolsrud (1935)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="225" to="225" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>, the scribe of these marginal notes is <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102584">Johannes Huseman</persName>, a notary in <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100070">Rome</placeName> ca <date when="1480"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>Penwork initials in brown ink over 2-12 lines. Some initials are extended along the margin, for example on <locus from="24v" to="24v" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="images">
                                    <p> Drawn notarial signs in brown ink. <locus from="149v" to="149v" scheme="folios"/>: Notarial sign of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102581">Conradus Gregorii</persName>. <locus from="150v" to="150v" scheme="folios"/>: Notarial sign of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102580">Ingemundus Petri</persName>. In circles the letters <quote xml:lang="la">In Pe</quote>. At the bottom: <quote xml:lang="la">Sudercopensis</quote>. <locus from="151r" to="151r" scheme="folios"/>: Notarial sign of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102582">Olaus Iohannis</persName>. At the bottom the letters <quote xml:lang="la">O io</quote>. <locus from="151v" to="151v" scheme="folios"/>: Notarial sign of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102583">Olaus Andreae</persName>, in the form of a tree. In a banner: <quote>Olauus Andree</quote>
                                    </p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
